Feature: Fix Stale Spec References
  As a developer maintaining the nmg-sdlc plugin
  I want all historical specs to describe the current implementation
  So that specs remain trustworthy artifacts without misleading references
     to removed OpenClaw paths, deleted skills, or the pre-v4.1.0 Discord integration

  Background:
    Given the cleanup has been applied across specs/ and scripts/sdlc-runner.mjs
    And this spec's own directory (feature-fix-stale-spec-references/) is excluded from drift sweeps

  # --- AC1: Stale openclaw/scripts/ paths ---

  Scenario: No stale openclaw/scripts/ paths remain in specs
    When I grep for "openclaw/scripts/" under specs/
    Then zero matches are returned
    And every former reference now points to "scripts/sdlc-runner.mjs" or "scripts/sdlc-config.example.json"

  # --- AC2: Removed OpenClaw-era skill names ---

  Scenario: generating-openclaw-config is replaced with init-config
    When I grep for "generating-openclaw-config" under specs/
    Then zero matches are returned
    And each replaced occurrence uses "init-config" with coherent surrounding prose

  Scenario: installing-openclaw-skill is removed entirely
    When I grep for "installing-openclaw-skill" under specs/
    Then zero matches are returned
    And surrounding prose reads coherently after each removal
    And no dangling list entries (e.g., "like , ") remain

  # --- AC3: Removed Discord integration ---

  Scenario: No postDiscord or discordChannelId references in specs
    When I grep for "postDiscord" or "discordChannelId" under specs/
    Then zero matches are returned

  Scenario: No case-insensitive "discord" references in specs
    When I grep for "discord" case-insensitively under specs/ excluding this spec's own directory
    Then zero matches are returned

  Scenario: Discord-dependent ACs are rewritten or deleted
    Given the bug-sdlc-runner-edge-case-fixes/ F2 section previously described the Atomics.wait in Discord retry
    When I read the F2 section after cleanup
    Then it describes the historical issue and notes the fix was applied (non-blocking sleep)
    And it does not name Discord

  # --- AC4: OpenClaw skill-sync and gateway-restart removed ---

  Scenario: No ~/.openclaw/ references in specs
    When I grep for "~/.openclaw/" under specs/
    Then zero matches are returned

  Scenario: feature-installing-locally-skill workflow is 5 steps, not 7
    Given feature-installing-locally-skill/design.md previously documented 7 steps including OpenClaw sync and gateway restart
    When I read the workflow after cleanup
    Then Steps 5 and 6 (OpenClaw sync, gateway restart) are removed
    And subsequent step numbers are renumbered accordingly

  Scenario: feature-migrate-project-skill AC6 and AC7 are removed
    Given AC6 checked ~/.openclaw/ and AC7 referenced /installing-openclaw-skill
    When I read requirements.md after cleanup
    Then neither AC6 nor AC7 remains
    And corresponding gherkin scenarios are also removed

  # --- AC5: Dangling feature-openclaw-runner-operations references ---

  Scenario: feature-openclaw-runner-operations references are redirected
    When I grep for "feature-openclaw-runner-operations" under specs/
    Then zero matches are returned
    And each former reference now points to "feature-add-skill-to-run-full-sdlc-pipeline-loop-from-within-claude-code"

  # --- AC6: Automatic major-version bump language ---

  Scenario: Automatic major-version bump language reflects v4.3.0 behavior
    Given v4.3.0 removed automatic major-version bumps triggered by milestone completion
    When I read any spec describing version-bump behavior
    Then the spec describes major bumps as manual only
    And no text claims milestone completion triggers a major bump

  # --- AC7: postDiscord removed from runner code ---

  Scenario: postDiscord is removed from sdlc-runner.mjs
    When I grep for "postDiscord" in scripts/sdlc-runner.mjs
    Then zero matches are returned

  Scenario: postDiscord is removed from runner Jest tests
    When I grep for "postDiscord" in scripts/__tests__/sdlc-runner.test.mjs
    Then zero matches are returned

  Scenario: Call sites log [STATUS] messages directly
    Given postDiscord was a pass-through that called log('[STATUS] …')
    When a call site formerly invoking "await postDiscord(msg)" is executed
    Then the log function receives the message with the "[STATUS]" prefix preserved
    And the orchestration log entry is identical to the pre-cleanup output

  Scenario: SIGTERM handler no longer chains .catch() on a synchronous log call
    Given the SIGTERM handler previously called postDiscord(...).catch(() => {}) fire-and-forget
    When the handler runs after cleanup
    Then it calls log('[STATUS] …') directly with no .catch() chain
    And it does not await the call

  Scenario: Jest suite passes after the runner change
    When I run "cd scripts && npm test"
    Then the exit code is 0
    And no tests fail or are newly skipped

  # --- AC8: Final drift sweep ---

  Scenario Outline: Every drift pattern returns zero matches after cleanup
    Given the cleanup is complete
    When I grep for <pattern> under <scope>
    Then zero matches are returned

    Examples:
      | pattern                                    | scope                                                                                  |
      | openclaw/scripts/                          | specs/                                                                         |
      | generating-openclaw-config                 | specs/                                                                         |
      | installing-openclaw-skill                  | specs/                                                                         |
      | postDiscord                                | specs/                                                                         |
      | discordChannelId                           | specs/                                                                         |
      | feature-openclaw-runner-operations         | specs/                                                                         |
      | ~/.openclaw/                               | specs/                                                                         |
      | openclaw (case-insensitive)                | specs/ excluding feature-fix-stale-spec-references/                             |
      | discord (case-insensitive)                 | specs/ excluding feature-fix-stale-spec-references/                             |
